  "event_preview": "The Indianapolis Motor Speedway Road Course is a 2.439-mile (3.926 km) 14-turn circuit built around the historic oval in Speedway, Indiana, first raced by IndyCar in 2014. The Sonsio Grand Prix is the sixth round of the 2026 NTT IndyCar Series season and the traditional curtain-raiser for the Month of May before Indy 500 qualifying begins the following weekend, run over 85 laps (207.3 miles). Reigning four-time champion Alex Palou has won the last three consecutive Sonsio Grand Prix events and could become only the fifth driver since 1946 to win four consecutive IndyCar races at the same track. Palou leads the championship standings by 17 points over Kyle Kirkwood heading into the weekend. Will Power, who has won five times at the IMS road course for Team Penske, enters for the first time representing Andretti Global, seeking to prove that his track record here transcends machinery. Three Rookie of the Year contenders — Caio Collet, Dennis Hauger and Mick Schumacher — will race on the IMS road course for the first time this weekend. The all-time qualifying record at the IMS road course belongs to Palou, who logged a 1:09.0004 in the 2024 Firestone Fast Six — the fastest lap ever turned in qualifying on the 2.439-mile layout. The race lap record is held by Palou as well, a 1:09.3417 set during his dominant 2025 victory, when he used a fresh set of alternate tyres in the Fast Six to seal pole before converting it into his third consecutive win.",
